The paper also mentions the use of deep metric learning and convolutional neural networks, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Hence, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of semantic-agnostic boundary detection and patch classification, which are related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the efficient collection of dataset, which could be related to data mining and information retrieval. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category.
